INSERT INTO `sports` (`Id`, `Post_Title`, `Post_Date`, `Post_Author`, `Post_Image`, `Post_Content`) VALUES
(1, 'Shakib 116 gives Bangladesh control', '2017-03-20 02:33:19', 'Jubair Ahmed Likhon', 'sakib100.jpg', 'Bangladesh made a memorable comeback in their 100th Test as their last five wickets nearly batted through the entire day. Shakib Al Hasan was at the centre of it all, making his fifth century in the format and ensuring his team took the first-innings lead for only the second time while batting second away from home.'),
(2, 'Barcelona draw Juventus, Real Madrid face Bayern in Champions League quarter-final draw', '2017-03-20 02:12:23', 'Tahrima Humayra', 'cl-qf-draw.jpg', 'The two Spanish giants have been given tough tests, while Leicester City face Atletico Madrid and Borussia Dortmund take on Ligue 1 side Monaco\r\n\r\nReigning champions Real Madrid will face Bayern Munich while Barcelona have drawn Juventus in the Champions League quarter-final draw.\r\n\r\nHaunted Wenger running into the last man he wants to face'),
(6, 'Iniesta rejects â‚¬35m offer from China', '2017-03-20 02:12:23', 'Shariful Islam', 'iniesta-bcn.jpg', 'Barcelona captain Andres Iniesta has turned down two offers from China, including one which offered a payment of 35 million euros per year after taxes, reports AS.\r\n\r\nAn unnamed Chinese Super League team is believed to have offered the Spaniard a whopping 35 million euros after taxes per year and also included other benefits such as the option to skip away games.\r\n\r\nIniesta has been engaged in contract negotiations with his contract due to expire in 2018, but he has refused the clubs first offer.\r\n\r\nClub president Josep Maria Bartomeu has suggested a deal of two more years for Iniesta, who will be 33 in May, but the deal was below-par from Iniestas standpoint. Another concern for Iniesta so far has been the lack of playtime and he is concerned with his influence waning in the squad, especially ahead of the 2018 World Cup in Russia.\r\n\r\n â€œI would like to take this opportunity to say, be it one thing or another, Iniesta and Barcelona will never have any kind of problem,â€ he said on Thursday, adding cryptically that â€œthis has been a different year.â€'),
(7, 'Hales, Root tons take England to record ODI win over Windies', '2017-03-20 02:12:23', 'Jubair Ahmed', 'root_10.jpg', 'England Alex Hales and Joe Root struck centuries as the tourists cruised to a series sweep with a massive 186-run victory over West Indies in the third and final one-day international at the Kensington Oval on Thursday.\r\n\r\nEngland, sent in to bat, amassed 328 all out in exactly 50 overs before restricting the hosts to 142 in 39.2 overs for their biggest ever win by runs over the Caribbean side.\r\n\r\nOpener Hales (110 from 107 balls), who returned to the team in place of Sam Billings after recovering from a broken hand, and Root (101 from 108 balls) put on 192 for the second wicket on an uneven pitch, a record for England against West Indies.\r\n\r\nThat laid the platform for the visiting side huge total, but they needed some power-hitting from Ben Stokes (34 from 20 balls) to ensure they made it past 300.\r\n\r\nSeamer Alzarri Joseph, 20, playing in just his third ODI, was the pick of the home bowlers with 4-76, including the wickets of Hayles and Root plus Moeen Ali for a first ball duck.'),
(8, 'Mashrafe signs for Rupganj', '2017-03-20 02:12:23', 'M H Sejan', 'mortaza.jpg', 'Mashrafe Bin Mortaza hogged the spotlight on the opening day of the two-day players transfer for the Dhaka Premier Division Cricket League at the Sher-e-Bangla National Stadium in Mirpur yesterday.\r\n\r\nThe Bangladesh limited-overs captain, who will fly for Colombo today to lead the Tigers in the three-match ODI and two-match T20I series against Sri Lanka, signed for Legends of Rupganj at almost the last second of the bourse after he had mistakenly gone to the Bangabandhu National Stadium -- where the event had been taking place for a long time before shifting to the home of cricket in Mirpur this season.\r\n\r\nMashrafe was excited that the transfer system returned to its traditional form after the player-by-choice system was used in last two seasons.'),
(9, 'Ronaldo expecting twins?', '2017-03-20 02:12:23', 'Shibly Sirajee', 'cr7_3.jpg', 'Football superstar Cristiano Ronaldo is about to become the father of twin boys, The Sun quoted a "family source" as saying.\r\n\r\nA surrogate mother based in the United States of America is in the final weeks of her pregnancy and is said to be expecting babies "very soon".\r\n\r\nThe 32-year-old Real Madrid forward has told his inner circle that the twins will be flown to his mansion on the outskirts of Madrid.\r\n\r\n"Cristiano and his family cannot wait to meet the new members of their clan," The Sun quoted the source as saying. \r\n\r\n"He likes to keep a tight lid on his private life but has told loved ones and close friends the baby boys are due to arrive very soon."\r\n'),
(10, 'India fightback after Smith epic knock', '2017-03-20 02:12:23', 'kowshik das', 'maxwell_2.jpg', 'All-rounder Glenn Maxwell hailed his "awesome" skipper Steve Smith after the duo 191-run partnership helped Australia post a formidable first innings total against India in the third Test in Ranchi Friday.\r\n\r\nMaxwell, returning to the five-day side after nearly three years in the wilderness, cracked his maiden Test century on day two but it was Smith unbeaten 178 that was the bedrock of the tourists 451.\r\n\r\nOpener Lokesh Rahul led India strong reply in the final session with the hosts ending the day on 120 for one. India still trail the visitors by 331 runs.\r\n\r\nMurali Vijay (42) and Cheteshwar Pujara (10) were batting at the break after Rahul was out caught behind for 67 off fast bowler Pat Cummins.\r\n\r\nRahul, who hit 9 fours in his 102-ball stay, registered his fourth fifty of the series to put on 91 runs with opening partner Vijay.\r\n\r\nBut it was the epic partnership between Smith and Maxwell that steered Australia to the highest total of the series so far after the visitors resumed the day on 299-4.'),
(11, 'PERFORMER OF THE DAY: SHAKIB AL HASAN', '2017-03-20 02:12:23', 'Ramzan Hussain', 'shakib1.jpg', 'What difference a day can make on a cricketer mindset and on the complexion of a whole game! On Thursday, Shakib Al Hasan, Bangladesh most illustrious cricketer, looked like a man at odds with everyone. He ruffled feathers of the opposition, looked extremely peeved while sitting at the dressing room and played every shot in anger while at the crease. Extremely lucky to have survived a madcap first eight deliveries, the all-rounder walked half-way towards the dressing room without even waiting for his partner. Yesterday, however, Shakib turned up a completely different man, mindful of his responsibilities as a senior statesman. He batted with extreme caution, in the process notching up his fifth Test century and more importantly guiding the team towards a healthy first-innings lead.'),
(12, 'Champions Trophy arrives', '2017-03-20 02:12:23', 'Paramita Saha', 'trophy_1.jpg', 'The official ICC Champions Trophy 2017, which is travelling to all eight participating nations will arrive in Dhaka today, a press release from the Bangladesh Cricket Board informed.\r\n\r\nThe 3.1 kg trophy will be on put on display at the Centre Court of the Jamuna Future Park from 11:00AM to 09:00PM today and tomorrow.\r\n\r\nOn March 20, the trophy will be taken to an iconic location in Dhaka for a photo shoot which will be followed by a visit to the Sher-e-Bangla National Cricket Stadium in Mirpur.'),
(13, 'Ramos takes Real two clear at top', '2017-03-20 02:12:23', 'Anindya Poddar', 'ramos_7.jpg', 'Real Madrid captain Sergio Ramos struck another late winner as the European champions usurped Barcelona at the top of La Liga with a hard-fought 2-1 win over Real Betis on Sunday.\r\n\r\nEarlier, Barca boss Luis Enrique accepted his side had struggled to shrug off the euphoria of a remarkable Champions League comeback against Paris Saint-Germain as the Spanish champions slumped to a shock 2-1 defeat at Deportivo la Coruna.\r\n\r\nVictory for Madrid moves Real two points clear of Barcelona and with a game in hand still to come.\r\n\r\nHowever, Madrid win was mired in controversy as goalkeeper Keylor Navas was extremely lucky to avoid an early red card before making a brilliant stoppage time save to deny Antonio Sanabria.'),
(14, 'A batsman cut out for Test cricket', '2017-03-20 02:12:23', 'Shibly Sirajee', 'mosaddek_8.jpg', 'Shakib Al Hasan may have grabbed all the headlines yesterday, but there was a debutant without whom Bangladesh would probably not have been able to accumulate the 129-run lead that placed the visitors ahead in the match.\r\n\r\nWhen Mushfiqur Rahim was dismissed for a well-played 52, Bangladesh were six down for 290 and still 48 runs adrift of Sri Lanka first innings score of 338. Things could easily have gone south from there, given Bangladesh penchant for collapses.\r\n\r\nBut unlike many who had walked onto the field in the Bangladesh helmet for the first time in Test cricket, Mosaddek Hossain came with serious first-class pedigree. Although he has played just 21 matches for Dhaka Division in the National Cricket League and East Zone in the Bangladesh Cricket League, he has scored seven centuries and five of them each -- 282, 250, 200 not out, 153 and 152 -- have been big ones, hinting at a propensity to bat long that has given him an average of 68.87 in 33 innings.\r\n\r\nThat facility for longer-version batting was evident during his innings of 75 off 155 balls with seven fours and two sixes. Apart from a few plays and misses off pacer Suranga Lakmal early on, he appeared completely untroubled. Unlike Shakib, Mosaddek did not offer any chances as he first put on 131 with Shakib -- a record for the seventh wicket for Bangladesh against Sri Lanka -- and then 33 for the eighth wicket with Mehedi Hasan Miraz which took Bangladesh lead past 100.'),
(15, 'Neymar out of Deportivo trip after PSG heroics', '2017-03-20 02:12:23', 'Tahrima Humayra', 'neymar-2.jpg', 'Barcelona forward Neymar will miss Sunday La Liga game at Deportivo La Coruna with a thigh problem, the club said on Saturday, depriving the champions of the hero of their stunning 6-1 midweek Champions League win over Paris St Germain.\r\n\r\nThe Brazilian, who scored two of Barca three late goals to complete a historic comeback from a 4-0 first-leg loss to the French champions, missed training on Saturday along with compatriot Rafinha who was suffering from gastroenteritis and has also been left out of the squad for Sunday game.\r\n\r\nBarca lead Real Madrid by a point at the top of the table while their arch-rivals have a game in hand and host struggling Real Betis hours after Barca visit Deportivo, who are unbeaten in their three games under new coach Pepe Mel.\r\n\r\nBarca manager Luis Enrique admitted his side faced a challenge in coming down from the cloud of emotion over their exploits on Wednesday but said he trusted his players to prepare appropriately for the game at Deportivo.\r\n\r\n"Without doubt it is something we have to be aware of and overcome but I trust the wisdom and sense of my players to realise that we are in the final stretch of the season and that we have everything to play for," Luis Enrique told reporters.'),
(16, 'Shakib puts Tigers on top', '2017-03-20 02:12:23', 'Prianka Islam', 'shakib_mosad.jpg', 'Call it resiliency or a perverse desire to prove naysayers wrong, but Bangladesh have made it a habit of turning in a stellar performance when their fans or critics least expect it. They did it on the first day of their 100th Test match at the P Sara Oval in Colombo after a 259-run thrashing less than a week ago in Galle, and they did it in even more spectacular fashion on the third day yesterday.\r\n\r\nIt was apt that the player who exemplifies the aforementioned qualities, Shakib Al Hasan, was one of the main actors in Bangladesh revival with his fifth Test century.\r\n\r\nAfter ending the second day with a spell of play that produced three wickets for six runs in seven balls, followed by batting from Shakib that could only be described as reckless as Bangladesh went to the close 124 runs behind and with five wickets in hand, the visitors ended the third day with a lead of 75, although Sri Lanka finished without loss with 52 runs on the board in 13 overs.\r\n\r\nThere was time enough for Dimuth Karunaratne to be dropped by skipper Mushfiqur Rahim off Subashis Roy off a difficult chance down the leg side, but it could not take much of the gloss off a wearing pitch and their position in the match.\r\n\r\nBefore that, Shakib century and a 75 on debut from Mosaddek Hossain carried Bangladesh to 467, a first-innings lead of 129, before Mosaddek wild heave missed the mark and he was stumped to become Sri Lanka skipper Rangana Herath 1,001st first-class wicket in the 135th over. Herath earlier became the 12th bowler from the subcontinent to reach the 1,000 first-class wicket landmark by getting Mustafizur Rahman leg-before in the 129th over.'),
(17, 'Tigers close in on rare away victory', '2017-03-20 02:12:23', 'Saymatul Tuba', 'shakib_73.jpg', 'Bangladesh are a few steps away from creating history in their 100th Test match. That may be a tempting way to see the situation that currently prevails in Colombo before Bangladesh attempt to take the two Sri Lankan wickets as early as possible today and minimise the hosts lead which currently stands at 139 in order to walk away with a share of the spoils in the two-match series, but if they manage to pull it off today, the enormity of the achievement may even exceed the significance of the 100th Test.\r\n\r\nFrom the debacle of the 259-run loss in the first Test, which in turn led to selection confusion, which then led to interference from every quarter that resulted in a profoundly divided touring party before this current Test, Bangladesh are on the cusp of eyeing a Test win against a team they have never beaten before and on a ground which has produced only innings-defeats for them in the past.'),
(18, 'This win started when we lost in Galle: Tamim Iqbal', '2017-03-20 02:12:23', 'kowshik das', 'tam_1.jpg', 'Tamim Iqbal, the man-of-the-match in Bangladeshâ€™s historic four-wicket win in the second Test match against Sri Lanka today, said the 259-run defeat in the first Test in Galle worked as an impetus for their win in Colombo.\r\n\r\nâ€œI think this win started when we lost the match in Galle,â€ Tamim elucidated when he spoke after the match.\r\n\r\nâ€œWe had a long chat with the coach, and the players stepped up. The way the bowlers bowled in the first innings was quite exceptional,â€ said Tamim, who scored a crucial 82-run knock in the second innings to lay the platform for victory.\r\n\r\nâ€œThat changed the whole thing. When you are chasing this kind of total, you have to be a little aggressive. Me and Sabbir were talking in the middle to look for runs. All came good except the last shot. The coach has backed us a lot. We are very lucky to have him,â€ the Bangladesh left-handed opener added.');

